Ok great, but what does that tell you if you compute the IQR?

Middle of the first half of data before the median subtracted from the middle of the second half of data after the median = interquartile range. (When there's an odd amount of numbers.)

Median of first half of numbers subtracted from median of second half of numbers = interquartile range (when there is an even amount of numbers.)
